-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Note on the eBPF objects
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
The programs under src/bpf/ call Linux kernel BPF helper functions that the
kernel exports only to GPL-compatible programs. Each BPF object therefore
declares the license string "Dual BSD/GPL" (via the char _license[] SEC
("license") variable) so the verifier permits those helper calls. This is a
per-object kernel requirement and does not widen the license of the project as
a whole, which is distributed under GPL-2.0-only as stated above. The userspace
sources carry SPDX headers of "BSD-2-Clause OR GPL-2.0"; when distributed as
part of this project they are conveyed under GPL-2.0.
